{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 160°C.","Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in hazelnuts. Transfer to a baking tray, bake for 8-10 minutes (160°C) until browned then leave on tray to cool. Meanwhile, cook cauliflower.","Place water and 1 tsp salt in mixing bowl, place Varoma dish into position then weigh in cauliflower. Cover Varoma and steam <nobr>20-25 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr> (see tip). Set covered Varoma aside.","Add fettuccine to mixing bowl, place covered Varoma back into position then cook <nobr>time indicated on packet\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr> or until al dente. Remove Varoma and set aside. Drain cooked fettuccine then transfer to a large bowl. Drizzle with ½ Tbsp oil, stir well and cover with foil to keep warm.","Place reserved roasted hazelnuts in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place garlic, onions and remaining 20 g oil in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <nobr>4 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add reserved steamed cauliflower, nutritional yeast, milk, lemon juice, 1 tsp salt and pepper. Heat <nobr>5 min\/80°C\/speed 2<\/nobr> then blend <nobr>30 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr> until smooth. Transfer to bowl with fettuccine and stir well with spatula to coat. Divide between serving plates, garnish with reserved chopped hazelnuts and parsley then serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["50 g blanched hazelnuts","1200 g water","2 tsp fine sea salt, or to taste","500 g cauliflower florets (2 cm)","250 g dried fettuccine","20 g extra virgin olive oil, plus ½ Tbsp for drizzling","2 garlic cloves","80 g onions, quartered","30 g nutritional yeast flakes","300 g almond milk or non-dairy milk of choice","15 g lemon juice","¼ tsp ground black pepper, or to taste","fresh parsley leaves, roughly chopped, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r328230","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-QTWOUDS